parameter.name: rate constant for CYP2E1 mRNA degradation

body.p: half life of cyp2e1 is reported to be 6 hrs (Roberts1995).Calculated by kd = ln(2)/t_half

Fraction absorbed, i.e., only a fraction of the chlorzoxazone in the intestinal lumen is absorbed. This parameter determines how much of the chlorzoxazone is excreted in every round of the enterohepatic circulation.
F_czx_abs of dose is absorbed. (1-F_czx_abs) is excreted in feces.

parameter.name: scaling factor for czx absorption rate

body.p: log(2) ~ 0.693 used for conversion of half-life injection time to injection rate.
production rate = degradation rate at baseline resulting in cyp2e1 = 1.0 dimensionless
Process of tablet/capsule dissolution in stomach/upper intestine and transport in the intestine. This is fast in case of solutions and slower in case of tablets/capsules.
Ethanol elimination via alcohol dehydrogenase in the liver. Due to saturation of enzyme (ethanol > ETHEL_KM) constant rate of ethanol elimination.
Ethanol stabilizes CYP2E1, i.e., the degradation rate is reduced.
